This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new method for learning binary classifiers from positive and unlabeled data. It may also be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as these fields often involve classification tasks and may benefit from the proposed method.
